name: Prolonged bleeding following procedure
description: Prolonged or protracted bleeding following an invasive procedure or intervention.

name: Factor: Tcfap2e; motif: TGCCCYNRGGCN
description: Factor: Tcfap2e; motif: TGCCCYNRGGCN

name: Macrothrombocytopenia
description: Macrothrombocytopenia

name: Abnormal oral mucosa morphology
description: Abnormality of the oral mucosa.

name: Prolonged bleeding after surgery
description: Bleeding that persists longer than the normal time following a surgical procedure.

name: Impaired platelet aggregation
description: An impairment in the rate and degree to which platelets aggregate after the addition of an agonist that stimulates platelet clumping. Platelet aggregation is measured using aggregometer to measure the optical density of platelet-rich plasma, whereby platelet aggregation causes the plasma to become more transparent.

name: blood coagulation
description: "The sequential process in which the multiple coagulation factors of the blood interact, ultimately resulting in the formation of an insoluble fibrin clot; it may be divided into three stages: stage 1, the formation of intrinsic and extrinsic prothrombin converting principle; stage 2, the formation of thrombin; stage 3, the formation of stable fibrin polymers." [PMID:30700128]

name: Abnormal platelet aggregation
description: An abnormality in the rate and degree to which platelets aggregate after the addition of an agonist that stimulates platelet clumping. Platelet aggregation is measured using aggregometer to measure the optical density of platelet-rich plasma, whereby platelet aggregation causes the plasma to become more transparent.

name: coagulation
description: "The process in which a fluid solution, or part of it, changes into a solid or semisolid mass." [ISBN:0198506732]

name: hemostasis
description: "The stopping of bleeding (loss of body fluid) or the arrest of the circulation to an organ or part." [ISBN:0198506732]

name: Spontaneous hematomas
description: Spontaneous development of hematomas (hematoma) or bruises without significant trauma.

name: Abnormal platelet membrane protein expression
description: Presence of reduced amount of a membrane protein on the cell membrane of platelets. This feature is typically measured by flow cytometry.

name: platelet alpha granule
description: "A secretory organelle found in blood platelets, which is unique in that it exhibits further compartmentalization and acquires its protein content via two distinct mechanisms: (1) biosynthesis predominantly at the megakaryocyte (MK) level (with some vestigial platelet synthesis) (e.g. platelet factor 4) and (2) endocytosis and pinocytosis at both the MK and circulating platelet levels (e.g. fibrinogen (Fg) and IgG)." [PMID:8467233]

name: Prolonged bleeding time
description: Prolongation of the time taken for a standardized skin cut of fixed depth and length to stop bleeding.

name: Platelet activation, signaling and aggregation
description: Platelet activation, signaling and aggregation

name: Formation of Fibrin Clot (Clotting Cascade)
description: Formation of Fibrin Clot (Clotting Cascade)

name: Impaired ristocetin-induced platelet aggregation
description: Abnormal response to ristocetin as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of ristocetin.

name: Increased mean platelet volume
description: Average platelet volume above the upper limit of the normal reference interval.

name: Abnormal platelet function
description: Any anomaly in the function of thrombocytes.

name: Epistaxis
description: Epistaxis, or nosebleed, refers to a hemorrhage localized in the nose.

name: Vascular skin abnormality
description: Vascular skin abnormality

name: glycoprotein Ib-IX-V complex
description: "A transmembrane signaling receptor complex found exclusively on platelets. Involved in haemostasis and thrombosis where it aids blood coagulation." [GOC:bhm, PMID:1730602, PMID:23336709, PMID:25297919]

name: Abnormal platelet volume
description: Anomalous size of platelets. Most normal sized platelets are 1.5 to 3 micrometers in diameter. Large platelets are 4 to 7 micrometers. Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers.

name: Giant platelets
description: Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers. The term giant platelet is used when the platelet is larger than the size of the average red cell in the field. (Description adapted from College of American Pathologists, Hematology Manual, 1998).

name: ITGA2b-ITGB3-CD9-GP1b-CD47 complex
description: ITGA2b-ITGB3-CD9-GP1b-CD47 complex
